It’s not a good idea to create this effect manually. It’s better to use a CSS code in the <style> tag to accomplish this. The code looks like this:

<style>

body {

font-family: serif;

font-size: 18px;

line-height: 21px;

color: #FFF;

font-weight: bold;

}

.boldText {

font-weight: bold;

}

</style>

<div class="boldText">Here is bold text</div>

You could also use tags in HTML like this:

<b>Here is bold text</b>

But this is slightly less flexible and will only work if you know the exact HTML code to use for your situation.

That’s a South African dish. It is named after the Afrikaans word “potjie” which means an iron pot, and it is prepared in that type of pot, hence the name. The dish consists of:

* tomatoes and green peppers, cut into small pieces;

* onion and garlic, cut into small pieces;

* grated cheddar cheese;

* meat stock, prepared as described below.

First the whole is cooked in a pot with the lid on, which is necessary for the dish to be properly cooked. Remove the lid and reduce the amount of heat and allow the dish to cook for a while longer. As the whole cooks, the steam from the pot will cook the top layer of the ingredients; to create the correct flavor the ingredients must be cooked well. Next add in the meat stock to let it cook a while longer. Finish with grated cheddar cheese.

The best school fundraisers are those that:  

1) have a wide appeal - can be enjoyed by lots of different kinds of people; 
2) require no special skills or knowledge of the school, i.e. if the school wants to do it, anyone can join in; 
3) give students a good incentive to get out and sell;
4) reduce student's out-of-pocket cost as much as possible;
5) make the parent/guardian contributions optional; 
6) will not burden students with taking time off from studies to do the fundraiser.

